# MITRE ATT&CK Mapping

## Overview

One of the primary objectives of this SOC Home Lab was not only to generate security alerts, but also to understand how real attacker behavior maps to the MITRE ATT&CK Framework.

MITRE ATT&CK is a globally recognized knowledge base used by Security Operations Centers (SOCs), threat hunters, incident responders, and detection engineers. Each attack technique has a unique Technique ID that allows defenders to classify attacker behavior and create better detections.

The table below shows how each activity performed during this project maps to the ATT&CK framework.

---

## ATT&CK Mapping

| Lab Activity | Command Used | MITRE Technique | Technique ID |
|--------------|-------------|-----------------|--------------|
| Display current user | `whoami` | System Owner/User Discovery | **T1033** |
| Display computer name | `hostname` | System Information Discovery | **T1082** |
| Enumerate local users | `net user` | Account Discovery: Local Account | **T1087.001** |
| Enumerate Administrators group | `net localgroup administrators` | Permission Groups Discovery: Local Groups | **T1069.001** |
| Display network configuration | `ipconfig` | System Network Configuration Discovery | **T1016** |
| List running processes | `Get-Process` | Process Discovery | **T1057** |
| Enumerate services | `Get-Service` | System Service Discovery | **T1007** |
| Browse files and folders | `Get-ChildItem C:\` | File and Directory Discovery | **T1083** |
| Enumerate local accounts | `Get-LocalUser` | Account Discovery | **T1087.001** |
| Execute PowerShell commands | PowerShell | Command and Scripting Interpreter: PowerShell | **T1059.001** |
| Execute CMD commands | Command Prompt | Command and Scripting Interpreter: Windows Command Shell | **T1059.003** |
| Create, modify and delete monitored files | `C:\SOC-Lab` | Indicator Removal / File Manipulation | **T1070** |
| Create Registry Run Key | `HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Run` | Boot or Logon Autostart Execution | **T1547.001** |
| Create a local user | `net user SOCAdmin Pass123! /add` | Create Account: Local Account | **T1136.001** |
| Add user to Administrators group | `net localgroup administrators SOCAdmin /add` | Valid Accounts: Local Accounts | **T1078.003** |

