## What I Learned

During this project I learned how common Windows commands used by both administrators and attackers are mapped to the MITRE ATT&CK framework.

I also learned that:

- Wazuh generates alerts based on detection rules rather than every command executed.
- A single command can belong to one or more MITRE ATT&CK techniques.
- Security analysts use ATT&CK mappings to understand attacker objectives and investigate incidents more efficiently.
- Detection rules help classify attacker behavior into standardized techniques used across the cybersecurity industry.

